Chop the woody ends off the @asparagus{200%g} and discard. Cut the asparagus into thirds. Cut the @mangetout{80%g} in half widthways. Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways then thinly slice widthways. Zest and halve the @lemon{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Finely chop the @chives{1%stalk}. Pick the @mint{1/2%bunch} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Bring a #large saucepan{} of water with a @salt{pinch} to the boil. Once boiling add the @penne pasta{200%g} and cook for ~{12%minutes}.

After the wheat pasta has been boiling for ~{10%minutes}, add the asparagus and mangetout to the boiling water, bring back to the boil and simmer for ~{2%minutes} more, then drain in a #colander{}. Drizzle over a little @oil{a little} and return to the saucepan off the heat.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @?oil{a drizzle} (and a knob of @?butter{knob} if you have some) in a #large frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the leek and cook until soft stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once the leek is soft, stir in the garlic and mint and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add the @creme fraiche{100%g} and the @water{3%tbsp} to the frying pan. Stir well to combine, bring to the boil then remove from the heat. Stir in the lemon zest, chives and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Season to taste with a squeeze of lemon juice, a pinch of salt and lots of @pepper{lots}.

Tip the sauce into the pan with the wheat pasta, asparagus and mangetout. Gently mix together until the wheat penne is completely coated, add a splash of water if the sauce is a bit thick. Taste and add more salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Serve in large #bowls{} and sprinkle over the remaining cheese. Enjoy!

